The paper deals with the combinatorial and geometrical aspects of subdividing a hexahedron into tetrahedra, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the use of these subdivisions in meshing methods, which relates to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and scientific computing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper presents visualizations of the tetrahedral meshes, which could be relevant to graphics (cs.GR).
